    <note>Chen(1) Shu(2) [83] Zhizhong's [34] father, Shixiu's [80] grandfather. Zhizhong's father-in-law was Xie(1) Bi [732]. The father-in-law of another son, Zhili [3056], was Wang(2) Qinruo [1768]. Since two sons (eldest and youngest) were both buried in Kaifeng, Xiangfu county,  and no Chens of this lineage seem to be cited in the Nanchang FZ, I am assuming that Shu made the move to Kaifeng. Nanchang FZ, 29.2a; XCB, 23.1b-2a, 37.9a-9b, 40.4b, 7a-8a, 43.12b, 13b, 45.2a, 13b, 47.21a; SHY:ZG, 5.23b, 64.11a; SHY:SH, 49.3a; SS, 267.6b-12a. CBD, 3, 2468-9.</note>
